Equality court to decide whether old flag constitutes hate speech **EDITOR'S NOTE: The livestream will resume at 2 pm **   JOHANNESBURG - The Equality Court is hearing an application brought by The Nelson Mandela Foundation on Monday against the display of the apartheid flag. It wants the court to declare displays of the old South Africa flag as hate speech, unfair discrimination and harassment based on race. The lobby group AfriForum challenges that stance.